caption: two days ago was the first time we went to this good restaurant. But It is definitely not the last time. We enjoyed the evening a lot with the generous service, with the high quality  food and booze and with the comfortable cost. We will no doubt come back in a short time.

This restaurant is certainly one of the coolest restaurants in the neighborhood. Anytime I come there I am very glad. They manage their very high  standard service and the highest level of food  they give. You are always happy with this place. Highly  recommended.

We arrived at this place for a meeting. This place was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was a winning. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we felt excellent. The food was just great. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Warmly recommended.
Picked up the classic ramen tonight for dinner and wow, so so good! Will definitely be trying the rest of the menu.
ordered takeout, loved it! 👌 salad has an amazing yuzu dressing that goes well with their pork dishes. 💣
I simply liked their dishes. I always get awesome service here. The place is always clean and the employees are always welcoming. Will come back again.

I adore this restaurant! They have first-rate meals, their menu is large, The chief cook in that restaurant is well trained, I enjoy very much eating all their dishes. The dishes are always fresh, the attitude towards the customers  is very good too. I frequently visit this place and I was never discontended. I recommend it with no hesitation.
This place is first-rate and spacious, the meals was delightful and the rates were very economical. quickly, efficient service and very affable staff. Highly recommended.
Kimchi ramen is my go to! The service at this location is great, both take-out and dine-in. Highly recommend!
Went for my friends birthday. She got the Korean ramen, very tasty. I got the bimimbap, also really good.
Always a delicious meal.
Great food, very kind employees, regularly great mood. They charge fair prices and the food quality is awesome. 5 stars.
Great food and drink

The food was amazing. The interior was rustic which made it very cozy and beautiful. Very Brooklyn. Also the parking can be a little tricky depending what time you go and which day of the week. But overall it was a good experience.

The Mokhito drink was really good, the dumplings too, however the Beef ramen was way too oily.  I asked if they could somehow water down the broth or change the broth and they “couldn’t” when replacing the broth is a simple task or watering it down. The menu should have a warning or Atleast be given verbally. Shame
Sooooo good! Classic Romen, (with bacon added) was devine with a rich broth that I couldn't get enough of.
Loved it.
The good was wonderful
Really good food! Wish there was more options for drinks!
Really good food and cocktails.

Came here under the suggestion of my friend. You walk in on the Flatbush ave entrance and must wait for the hostess to greet you. To sit at a table we needed a reservation however we arrived within a sweet spot time. Next reservation coming in was in an hour and half. More than enough time to grab some dinner. For drinks we had the ginger plum cold tea. I feel in love with the first taste (also available in hot)  They don't deal with milk products so no half and half available. No white rice available only purple but tastes like brown rice . The glasses offered for drinking water were dirty so I have to give them back to our waiter.  Open kitchen so the entire restaurant is engulfed in a clear  billow of korean aroma
Happy hour was such a hit. I was able to try a buncha things w.o breaking the bank. I'm definitely going back for ramen
Good food and some very interetsring mixed drinks!
Update your hours
I eat here a lot since I work right next to it. I got to say the service is always fantastic and they keep the place clean consistently. Rates are convenient and they serve sizeable portions.
Everything felt stale and flavorless. It used to be good last time I came here last year maybe. Something’s changed. Couldnt eat any more than one bite of anything.
Watermelon Cold Noodles is perfect for summer.
Great great great spot - Kelly our waitress was fantastic as well. Had the veggie dumplings, kimchi, Brussels sprouts and vegan miso ramen, everything was excellent!
Great taste and fusion feel to ramen. Love the quaint feel and hip vibe
Great happy hour with $5 apps and drink specials and everything we ate was delicious!

I've never met a ramen place I didn't like including this one! Pricy drinks but fairly priced ramen and the dumpling appetizers were delish. Got a great dinner out with a friend for 20 bucks (sans drink).
Loved the happy hour menu but the drinks were too sugary for my tastes. Will come back , the wings and dumplings were delicious
The place is nice, service is good, but the food is mediocre. We are the bibibmap with beef, wasn't as good as in other restaurants.

I really don't usually leave a review, but man I wish I told a waiter that food just taste so old and stale! Rice was rock hard, the meat tasted like its 2 weeks old frozen just microwaved, as well as side dishes. It's not matter of them tasting bad, it's just disrespectful to serve such stale food to customers..
I didn't go there to eat, and those soju cocktails sneak up on you. 👌🏾

I personally did not enjoy the bibimbap. The disco fries were excellent though. The people I was dining with also were a bit underwhelmed, but that could be a taste preference? I do enjoy all other Asian food so I was surprised I didnt enjoy this Korean food as well. The waiters are helpful but will make you think everything is amazing which understandably their job but the food did not live up to the hype.

I always love mokbar. This is the first time at this location. Its a bit hidden and i think perhaps i used a back door with no sign. As usual the food was amazing. I always get the bulgogi ramen and pot stickers. This is my favorite place for korean ramen. The service could be a bit better that day but it wasnt bad, just not present as much as id like. Thats not the norm though.
Superb. Clean, very pleasant staff. Food was out of this world. I had kimchi ramen and was so good. This place will not disappoint!
Great Korean food near Barclays. Ho Cakes are a superb.
one of my fave spots in BK!
Staff was great. Food was underwhelming.

pajeon is out of this world. Their vegan miso soup is also really good; not my favorite ramen in the city, but really good. Their cocktails are creative and delightful; a little on the sweet side. Only one of their kimchis is vegan, the cucumber one, and it's kinda disappointing. Service is great.
Nice place, nice staff, very friendly,food is great ,many side dishes like can be refilled ,better order by group order. all dishes were good and my family enjoyed it.
Great food, service and ambiance

One of the best ramen place in downtown Brooklyn. Ramen Broth is flavorful, other popular Korean dishes are also available,  service is great and they exemplified the mood of BK where young kids or babies 👶 are not frown upon but to be entertained and coddled.

Very cozy as you walk in. Open kitchen, with several booths and a back room with dining tables. Dont expect your traditional korean food, instead enjoy the chef daily creative fusion korean dishes. The noodles soup base was tasty, had enough flavor and seasonings. The beef bulgogi served on the hot plate was excellent. Great place to have a beer or spirits to accompany a bowl of noodles. Very reasonable prices. Definitely will revisit.
Excellent food. A little pricey, but not too bad. Service was friendly and attentive.
Good high quality
What a great find! Really yummy korean food in an intimate setting. Great date spot.
Food not great honestly. Don’t understand the good reviews...
Very friendly service, great food, and surprisingly good prices .
Good food and great drinks .. awesome bartender
Service was great and the food was delicious. Next time I look forward to trying some soju and entree dishes.
Awesome cocktails, good customer service and tasty food.
Delicious ramen, appetizers and tasty cocktails. Can get pretty pricey especially with drinks but if you're in the mood for excellent ramen this is the best in the area

Stopped by for a beer for happy hour with a coworker and came across this gem that I recognized on their menu on a hot summer day that I had to get. Cold soybean noodle soup or their take on 콩국수. Normally it’s not ramen noodles but it still was amazing. Broth was nutty and salty in the best possible way. One of the best things I’ve eaten and still under the radar. I hope they bring it back every summer!
Food was decent.  It's Korean fusion. Service was not good tonight.

Their Budaejjigae Ramen was a bit of a disappointment for me, but I love all of their cold noodles! the watermelon is a bit overrated and overpriced ($25?!) but still good. I'd recommend the soy broth
Good Concept but Not So Good Taste
Nice small restaurant with good food. Great music. All-around good place to go for a quick bite.
Food was very good. Service was excellent
They've got some interesting flavors but it lacks depth
Super yummy seasonings and flavors, definitely some things I've never tried before. Also great service, very friendly people!

I really like this place. The staff are friendly and attentive, and the quality of my food was very good. It's a little more expensive than I would've preferred for the items I got, but very tasty and well-prepared nonetheless. I got the mok wings and they were delicious. The kalbi dumplings are also somethinf I'd recommend. Next time I'll come try the ramen! Heard that's one of the biggest sellers.
Awesome place to go
Nice place, good cocktails, good service. Bibimbap and ramen were ok. Good to know the 5-7 is only for high tables.
I enjoyed the drinks at this place very much. My sister will be turning 21 soon, so i'm gonna take her here for one of her many celebrations.

Absolutely recommend if you're open minded and have a taste for spicy korean foods! Hot mushroom tofu soup was on point as well as all the complimentary side dishes they offer! I forgot what my wife ordered but it came in a hot stone bowl and you give it a mix. It was amazing 2 thumbs up.

When they sat us down , no menu or water was given. After 2 or 5 mins or so , we had to wave for someone to give us the menu and water..hmm We then ordered our food but my friends sprite came long after my gingerale,  why? It's no martini or other special drink.  It's just a poured half can of soda and ice in a glass.  And again my food came lOng before hers and the Bulgogi was burnt, for the both of us and our dishes had a bitter aftertaste.  Mind you, we both have had Korean food plenty of times.  Sadly, it only looks good , but it does not taste good.  The taste of chicken wings lacked also.  I am a big noodle and ramen fanatic and this is literally the first time that made me not like ramen. My friend was devastated and I was disappointed.  Sorry.
Fantastic Korean ramen, excellent pickled bits. Have a Korean beer on draft.

Mokbar made us feel at home. We made a 7 o clock appointment and were quickly seated. Our drinks, the Gypsy Dreams and the Dark & Ginger, arrived right on time and so did our appetizer, tteobokai. Our ramen had so many subtle flavor bursts that we had to take a pause and reflect. The drinks were the same way. This is very thoughtful food that is thoughtfully prepared.
Amazing food

Went for lunch and the experience was great overall. Food was tasty, more than enough, drinks were also good. They had just started the lunch menu so that's probably why more people weren't there. I don't see why lunch wouldn't be successful. Will definitely be back.

Delicious Korean food and cocktails. I lived in Korea for years so I’m picky. Also a very accommodating staff, who were very generous and flexible in seating our party, which included a baby. Great service!
Great restaurant, unassuming and non-pretentious Korean place with delicious food. Chef Minji knows his stuff.
Waited and waited. They over booked and didnt see a waiter for 30 min.. place is whack
(Translated by Google) Friendly and delicious. I have a willingness to visit again.  (Original) 친절하고 맛있어요 또 방문할 의사있어욤
Very informative staff and delicious food!
Absolutely amazing - food, service, ambiance. Really creative menu and generous portions. Our waiter explained everything and was just as funny as he was hospitable. Will be back very soon!
Food solid. Staff awesome and kid friendly
The best place
I had the Army Ramen. It was delicious and filling. I ate alone and sat at the bar. The bartender lady was the friendliest bartender I’ve ever met. Will come back!
Food was good. Nice cozy spot.
Bleh. The "vegan" ramen was spaghetti. Yuck.
Loved it! Authentic Korean with great ambiance and good service
Good and drinks were fantastic, would just again in a heartbeat.
Really great sizzling dishes and interesting drinks
The place is nice but is is really hot inside. I know better Korean places around.
A bit on the expensive side, but worth every penny! The best time to go is for brunch, and dinner is a really busy time.
Found this place by accident.  It was a perfect find!
Very accommodating staff, food is good and healthy.
Meh, it's fusion.  Kimchis were really good.

Fantastic environment and food. Very festive right now, with great music, really nice atmosphere, splendid food,, and really interesting happy hour. Great location, with lots to do nearby before or after you eat.
Very tasty food, great menu, drinks looks good too.

My rice cake in my K-pop chicken  was under cooked. I was so excited to try this place the video i saw on youtube and the pics on the website really made it look like it was going to be quite an experience. Meal presentation was very nice, prices were ok, i didnt like that you had to pay extra for banchan which im very accustomed getting along with any meal ordered at Korean restaurants i go to in Ga. On a whole kool looking space, service was good, first time eating Korean food its ok, but if you've eaten at other more authentic places you might be disappointed. Miss Korea in korea town is excellent!

I came here alone on a Monday night and received excellent service. I got 2 appetizers instead of a meal because the app list was so enticing, and they were both delicious and filling. Definitely not stingy portions, solid cocktails, personable service,  and a great bartender. With such an inventive menu, I can't wait to come back and try more.
Great service! Helped us understand how spicy each dish we were ordering would be as well as understanding some of the cocktails.

The modern take on Korean food offered by this restaurant misses the mark and fails to deliver. I would not recommend this as a place for anyone. The wait staff is also lacking. We had an awkward time being seated and served. Instant shin ramen is better than their classic ramen. Their kimchi jaeyook was okay but not good enough to recommend over other restaurants. It took us too long to get the check considering how few people were in the restaurant. This place is a pass.

Korean Jipbap menu was great to see in this fancy fusion K restaurant! Price is really reasonable! I ordered fish of the day for lunch. It was grilled perfectly and it went well with a bowl of rice and neat side dishes. My all time favorite! It's just like real homemade food! Check it out folks!!

I have eaten at the Mokbar in Chelsea Market several times and was ecstatic to learn they were opening a standalone location in Brooklyn. Located near the Barclay's Center, Mokbar will not disappoint. As an enjoyer of ramen, I especially love the Kimche Jjigae. The decor is wonderful and staff friendly. I recommend this place to everyone!
Excellent Korean Ramen and Bibimbap. Prices were good and very large portions. Service was not as attentive as I would like, but still friendly and helpful.

The food was not as good as anticipated. The flavors strayed too far from traditional korean food and it was overwhelming to the palate. The drinks were okay, nothing too exciting. I would not go back.
Prettygood ramen, service was really great as well.
All food arrived lukewarm.
Fantastic Korean fusion menu with great cocktails

The food is a little too "fusion" for me in that it caters to a western audience by playing up and overcharging for culinary elements that are pretty normal if you go any Korean restaurant.  Food takes a while to come out of the kitchen, and this was when the restaurant was not even full.  Also a little odd that a Korean restaurant employs nearly all caucasian waitstaff that don't seem to really understand or have been exposed to Korean or Asian food.  The waitstaff were friendly but altogether completely ignorant of Korean cuisine outside what they were told about the menu.

The service was generally good and accommodating for a busy Sunday night. We arrived around 8:30 and waited for about 10 minutes. Overall the food wasn't bad. The plating is much nicer than what you would normally get in K-Town, but other than that I'd need to go back a few more times to see if I appreciate their food more. Otherwise, once in a while it's a good spot to hit up.  Extra kudos to the staff simply because they hustled in a busy place, and kept on top of the food, which can get lost in the bustle.

YUM! So glad that Mokbar opened in the neighborhood. Great mandoo! We loved the Bi Bim Bop Royale -- I added pork to this! -- and the KPop Chicken. Get the Ho Cake which is crispy dough filled with pork goodness! Mung Bean Cake is tasty too!

Great food in a fun place. The service was excellent - we mentioned that we were vegetarian and they were careful with the way they prepared each dish. I didn't really understand what "Korean comfort food" was describing, but the tofu steak was exactly that. The dumplings were great as well. The miso ramen was good, but probably suffers in comparison with Chuko. The price was fine for the neighborhood, and we can't wait to go back.

Better than good, short of excellent.  Intresting meal,  slightly expensive.  The place is still trying to get it's legs underneath itself.  Japchai Dumplings were underwhelming, but most everything else was flavorfully and fresh.  I will be back to try more apps.

Sadly my first visit here was underwhelming. It took the two of us 45 minutes to get our food and when it arrived it was not even that hot. The classic ramen had delicious fillings, but the broth was a little lackluster. The bibimbap was fairly good, but it's nice when the rice is a different temperature than the rest of the ingredients rather than all room temp. We were there for the soft opening so I expected a few kinks, here's to hoping that they are ironed out sooner than later.
